BLURBS_A:
The horizontal lines are the fret markers of the guitar. The spaces between them are the frets.

The vertical lines are the strings. The fattest string is on the left; the skinniest string is on the right.

The dots indicate on which frets & strings to place your fingers.

The numbers below the diagram indicate which finger to use, where:
1 = index finger;
2 = middle finger;
3 = ring finger;
4 = pinky finger;
0 = no finger used, string played open;
X = string not used

There is sometimes a number to the left of the top fret which indicates that those dots start on that fret number.
